1
00:02:00,286 --> 00:02:05,542
♪♪♪

2
00:02:26,513 --> 00:02:27,514
(male #1)
Cause of death?

3
00:02:27,897 --> 00:02:30,316
Asthma, heart attack,
they're not sure.

4
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:31,317
His name was Phillip Taylor.

5
00:02:31,818 --> 00:02:33,820
The little boy's Joshua.
It's his son.

6
00:02:34,070 --> 00:02:35,855
Has the kid said anything?

7
00:02:35,855 --> 00:02:36,856
Oh, he's devastated.

8
00:02:36,856 --> 00:02:38,825
He's not saying much
of anything right now.

9
00:02:39,409 --> 00:02:41,911
So who are they?

10
00:02:41,911 --> 00:02:43,913
Lady on the left
is the neighbor.

11
00:02:44,414 --> 00:02:45,915
The other one is Anna.

12
00:02:45,915 --> 00:02:47,417
She's a maid.

13
00:02:47,417 --> 00:02:48,418
She doesn't speak
a lot of English,

14
00:02:48,418 --> 00:02:50,420
but from what I can tell
she was upstairs cleaning,

15
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:53,957
heard the dogs barking, ran
downstairs, and called us.

16
00:02:54,457 --> 00:02:56,459
Sir, I found an address
book of the deceased,

17
00:02:56,960 --> 00:02:59,462
a few other documents
as well.

18
00:02:59,963 --> 00:03:01,464
Okay, good.

19
00:03:01,464 --> 00:03:04,968
Let's go through it, find
a friend or coworker, anybody.

20
00:03:04,968 --> 00:03:05,969
Poor kid.

21
00:03:05,969 --> 00:03:07,720
No immediate family,
now this?

22
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:11,558
(female #1)
There's a Henry
and Lucille Bauman listed here.

23
00:03:12,058 --> 00:03:13,109
Is there
a phone number?

24
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:16,029
Yeah, I got
a phone number right here.

25
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:18,031
Contact them
both immediately.

26
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:19,983
Inform them
of the situation.

27
00:03:19,983 --> 00:03:22,535
Stay with the boy
and get him somewhere safe.

28
00:03:22,535 --> 00:03:26,372
I'll finish out the reports,
meet you back at the office.

29
00:03:26,873 --> 00:03:30,710
♪♪♪

30
00:03:30,710 --> 00:03:33,713
(Joshua)
I miss you, Dad.

31
00:03:39,469 --> 00:03:44,807
I couldn't ever imagine
feeling so empty and so alone.

32
00:03:45,842 --> 00:03:48,761
But here I am.

33
00:03:56,819 --> 00:03:58,771
I tried to reach him!

34
00:03:58,771 --> 00:04:00,773
I tried.
I really did!

35
00:04:01,274 --> 00:04:03,610
Oh, Joshua,
I know you did.

36
00:04:03,610 --> 00:04:05,745
I know.

37
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:09,365
It's going to be
all right now.

38
00:04:09,365 --> 00:04:13,036
It's going to be
all right.

39
00:04:15,004 --> 00:04:17,423
Christopher, would you please
take Joshua inside

40
00:04:17,423 --> 00:04:18,925
and help him get settled?

41
00:04:19,342 --> 00:04:21,794
Yes, ma'am.

42
00:04:24,297 --> 00:04:25,298
(female #2)
Mrs. Lucille Bauman?

43
00:04:25,798 --> 00:04:27,216
I'm Karen Green, the caseworker
for the adoption agency,

44
00:04:27,216 --> 00:04:31,220
and this is Mr. Richard Smith,
the attorney for the Taylors.

45
00:04:31,220 --> 00:04:34,107
Mrs. Bauman, we spoke
earlier on the phone today.

46
00:04:34,274 --> 00:04:35,858
Yes.
Nice to meet you both.

47
00:04:35,858 --> 00:04:36,859
My husband's on his way home.

48
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,562
Would you like to come
in and take a seat?

49
00:04:39,562 --> 00:04:40,647
No thanks, Mrs. Bauman.

50
00:04:41,147 --> 00:04:42,148
We won't be very long.

51
00:04:42,148 --> 00:04:43,366
I really hate
that we had to meet

52
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:45,451
under such circumstances
as this.

53
00:04:45,451 --> 00:04:48,454
Well, Phillip
was very dear to us

54
00:04:48,454 --> 00:04:50,456
and we're going to miss
him dearly.

55
00:04:50,456 --> 00:04:52,542
Where do we go
from here?

56
00:04:52,542 --> 00:04:54,544
Mrs. Bauman, do you recall
the adoption agreement that you

57
00:04:54,544 --> 00:04:58,581
and your husband made to serve
as caretakers for Joshua

58
00:04:58,581 --> 00:05:00,667
that it stated
in Mr. Phillip's will?

59
00:05:00,667 --> 00:05:02,385
Yes, we do recall.

60
00:05:02,385 --> 00:05:04,470
Mrs. Bauman, what's
the zip code here?

61
00:05:04,470 --> 00:05:06,472
78218.

62
00:05:06,472 --> 00:05:10,510
You know, it's really great
for Joshua that both families

63
00:05:10,510 --> 00:05:12,512
had this agreement worked out.

64
00:05:12,512 --> 00:05:14,397
Frankly, many children
end up with families

65
00:05:14,397 --> 00:05:16,182
that they don't even know.

66
00:05:16,182 --> 00:05:19,185
I'm just so glad
that we could help Joshua.

67
00:05:19,185 --> 00:05:20,770
Ma'am, if you would sign
this release form

68
00:05:20,770 --> 00:05:23,272
for the release of Joshua.

69
00:05:24,774 --> 00:05:25,775
And you do have our deepest
condolences on this

70
00:05:26,275 --> 00:05:28,277
unexpected tragedy
of your friend.

71
00:05:30,196 --> 00:05:31,197
Thank you.

72
00:05:31,698 --> 00:05:33,583
Is there anything that
we can do at the house?

73
00:05:33,866 --> 00:05:36,619
Actually, Mrs. Bauman,
the house is in foreclosure.

74
00:05:36,619 --> 00:05:40,173
Joshua did have time to get
his things out of the house

75
00:05:40,173 --> 00:05:42,759
that he needed,
and frankly, the bank

76
00:05:42,759 --> 00:05:45,261
has taken over possession
of the home.

77
00:05:45,261 --> 00:05:47,263
Mrs. Bauman, if this is
too much of a burden

78
00:05:47,263 --> 00:05:48,431
for you all at once--

79
00:05:48,431 --> 00:05:53,519
Ms. Greene, all my burdens
have been taken to the cross.

80
00:05:53,519 --> 00:05:55,104
Well, that's great
to know, Mrs. Bauman.

81
00:05:55,605 --> 00:05:56,773
And I'm sure Joshua
is in great hands.

82
00:05:57,357 --> 00:05:58,858
Again, you have
our condolences.

83
00:05:58,858 --> 00:06:00,893
Thank you so much.

84
00:06:00,893 --> 00:06:03,479
Mrs. Bauman, if you
or your husband need anything,

85
00:06:03,479 --> 00:06:06,783
anything at all, don't
hesitate to give us a call.

86
00:06:06,783 --> 00:06:07,784
There's my card.

87
00:06:07,784 --> 00:06:08,785
Thank you both.
And God bless you.

88
00:06:08,785 --> 00:06:11,037
Thank you.

89
00:06:16,826 --> 00:06:20,963
Hey, Joshua, I'm really
sorry about your dad.

90
00:06:20,963 --> 00:06:21,798
Yeah.

91
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:24,000
Thanks.

92
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,585
Aren't you angry?

93
00:06:25,585 --> 00:06:27,754
I mean,
both of your parents?

94
00:06:27,754 --> 00:06:28,721
Kind of.

95
00:06:28,721 --> 00:06:30,223
Sort of.

96
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:32,141
You, your dad
were always at church

97
00:06:32,642 --> 00:06:35,094
and you never missed
Sunday school.

98
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:38,398
So why would God take them
both away from you like that?

99
00:06:38,898 --> 00:06:42,318
My father always told me,
"God has a purpose

100
00:06:42,318 --> 00:06:47,690
for all things even if we
don't understand it."

101
00:06:47,690 --> 00:06:50,743
Well, I don't understand.

102
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:53,246
Anyway, come on.

103
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:54,947
Let's play a board game.

104
00:06:54,947 --> 00:06:56,365
Why?

105
00:06:56,365 --> 00:06:58,751
You always beat me
in everything we play.

106
00:06:59,285 --> 00:07:00,703
'Kay.

107
00:07:00,703 --> 00:07:04,257
Under the circumstances,
I'll be nice.

108
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:05,091
This time only.

109
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:07,844
Nah.
I'm just tired.

110
00:07:07,844 --> 00:07:10,096
Thanks, though.

111
00:07:12,515 --> 00:07:17,603
♪♪♪

112
00:07:24,861 --> 00:07:27,864
Obey...

113
00:07:28,865 --> 00:07:33,152
God's Word.

114
00:07:35,872 --> 00:07:38,791
No!

115
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:40,793
Daddy!

116
00:07:41,294 --> 00:07:43,296
No!

117
00:08:04,317 --> 00:08:19,282
♪♪♪

118
00:08:26,756 --> 00:08:27,757
[applauding]

119
00:08:27,757 --> 00:08:31,844
Let's give it up one more
time for Sound of Praise.

120
00:08:32,345 --> 00:08:36,349
[applauding]

121
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:39,852
Well, I want to thank
everybody for coming out today

122
00:08:39,852 --> 00:08:43,689
to the third annual Attorneys
for Christ Association Luncheon.

123
00:08:43,689 --> 00:08:46,976
Let me bring up here the
newest chairman of the AFCA,

124
00:08:47,393 --> 00:08:50,479
Mr. Christopher Bauman.

125
00:08:50,980 --> 00:08:54,984
[applauding]

126
00:08:54,984 --> 00:08:57,486
Thank you.

127
00:08:57,987 --> 00:09:00,990
Thank you very much
for this award.

128
00:09:00,990 --> 00:09:03,993
We look forward to doing
bigger and brighter things

129
00:09:03,993 --> 00:09:06,045
in the Seguin Community.

130
00:09:06,045 --> 00:09:07,079
Thank you very much.

131
00:09:07,079 --> 00:09:11,584
[applauding]

132
00:09:16,589 --> 00:09:18,591
(male #2)
Well, if it isn't
the most famous,

133
00:09:18,591 --> 00:09:20,092
competent lawyer
of Seguin, Texas.

134
00:09:20,092 --> 00:09:22,094
Walter, how are you?

135
00:09:22,094 --> 00:09:24,597
Doing good.

136
00:09:25,097 --> 00:09:28,317
Your client,
Jonathan Chase,

137
00:09:28,317 --> 00:09:30,236
hasn't accepted
the plea bargain.

138
00:09:30,236 --> 00:09:32,154
What's the deal?

139
00:09:32,154 --> 00:09:33,072
He'll plea.

140
00:09:33,072 --> 00:09:35,524
Just give him some time.

141
00:09:37,493 --> 00:09:39,946
I hope so.

142
00:09:41,831 --> 00:09:42,832
Well, speaking of time,
I'm sorry Walter,

143
00:09:42,832 --> 00:09:45,701
but there's another
meeting I have to attend.

144
00:09:45,701 --> 00:09:47,203
It was good
seeing you again.

145
00:09:47,703 --> 00:09:48,704
Well, don't let
me hold you up.

146
00:09:49,205 --> 00:09:50,206
It's good to see you
too, Christopher.

147
00:09:50,206 --> 00:09:52,592
Take care.

148
00:09:54,677 --> 00:09:58,681
♪♪♪

149
00:10:04,136 --> 00:10:06,639
♪ I know
the right words to say ♪

150
00:10:06,639 --> 00:10:08,140
♪ to paint a pretty picture ♪

151
00:10:08,140 --> 00:10:12,144
♪ to make you see
like I got it all together ♪

152
00:10:12,144 --> 00:10:14,647
♪ yeah ♪

153
00:10:14,647 --> 00:10:16,148
♪ Knowing good and well ♪

154
00:10:16,148 --> 00:10:19,151
♪ there's a war
going on inside of me ♪

155
00:10:19,652 --> 00:10:21,654
♪ between the man
that I used to be ♪

156
00:10:21,654 --> 00:10:23,155
♪ and the man
that I'm becoming ♪

157
00:10:23,155 --> 00:10:27,410
♪ there's something's
got to give ♪♪

158
00:10:27,410 --> 00:10:29,328
[phone ringing]

159
00:10:29,328 --> 00:10:30,579
Hello?

160
00:10:31,163 --> 00:10:31,664
Hey, baby.

161
00:10:31,664 --> 00:10:34,166
Hey.
You get to the station yet?

162
00:10:34,166 --> 00:10:35,167
Yeah, I'm here.

163
00:10:35,551 --> 00:10:36,552
Well, I've been trying
to call you

164
00:10:36,552 --> 00:10:37,753
for like the last 2 hours.

165
00:10:37,753 --> 00:10:40,339
The association had a brief
meeting at the Jazz Spot.

166
00:10:40,339 --> 00:10:42,808
The Jazz Spot?

167
00:10:42,808 --> 00:10:44,310
What about the home spot?

168
00:10:44,310 --> 00:10:47,563
Lunch here, 12:30?

169
00:10:47,563 --> 00:10:50,149
You know, it just so happens
to be that I'm your wife

170
00:10:50,149 --> 00:10:53,352
and not just
one of your clients.

171
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:55,571
No, that's all right.
Thanks a lot.

172
00:11:01,327 --> 00:11:02,411
Yes sir, what
can I get for you?

173
00:11:02,411 --> 00:11:03,913
Hot dog.

174
00:11:03,913 --> 00:11:05,915
All right, well I do them
all kinds of different ways.

175
00:11:05,915 --> 00:11:06,916
I've got some
bacon wrapped-- Just mustard.

176
00:11:07,416 --> 00:11:08,918
You got it.

177
00:11:09,418 --> 00:11:13,089
[train whistle sounding]

178
00:11:13,589 --> 00:11:14,590
I'm going to fix
this up for you.

179
00:11:14,590 --> 00:11:16,592
You be careful
with that nice suit

180
00:11:16,592 --> 00:11:17,593
and this mustard, all right?

181
00:11:18,094 --> 00:11:19,095
Next time you come through
here, you try my bacon wrap.

182
00:11:19,595 --> 00:11:21,047
They are fantastic.

183
00:11:22,548 --> 00:11:24,800
That's going to be $4, sir.

184
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:25,885
Keep the change.

185
00:11:25,885 --> 00:11:28,387
Appreciate that.
You be safe.

186
00:11:42,702 --> 00:11:45,154
(male #3)
I'll see y'all soon, okay?
(female #3)
Be careful, okay?

187
00:11:45,154 --> 00:11:47,740
I will.
I love you, Cameron.

188
00:12:07,143 --> 00:12:09,645
Well, well, if it
ain't my long lost,

189
00:12:10,146 --> 00:12:12,648
no time to see me
big brother.

190
00:12:12,648 --> 00:12:14,650
What's happening, man?

191
00:12:14,650 --> 00:12:16,652
Very busy man.

192
00:12:16,652 --> 00:12:18,154
It's good to see you,
man.

193
00:12:18,654 --> 00:12:20,156
Good to see
you too, free man.

194
00:12:20,156 --> 00:12:22,158
Yeah, right. Welcome home.

195
00:12:22,658 --> 00:12:23,659
How's Mama?

196
00:12:23,659 --> 00:12:25,161
Well, you know Mom.
She's fine.

197
00:12:25,161 --> 00:12:27,696
Still trying to win
everyone over to the Lord.

198
00:12:27,696 --> 00:12:29,198
Yeah, so what
about you, man?

199
00:12:29,198 --> 00:12:30,199
You been won over?

200
00:12:30,199 --> 00:12:32,785
Look, Josh, it's been
a long time since we've seen

201
00:12:32,785 --> 00:12:34,787
one another,
11 years to be exact.

202
00:12:35,287 --> 00:12:38,791
When we were younger,
I never missed Sunday school,

203
00:12:38,791 --> 00:12:40,292
I never missed
a youth retreat.

204
00:12:40,292 --> 00:12:42,678
So I don't need church.

205
00:12:42,678 --> 00:12:44,180
I'm doing just fine.

206
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:48,350
So to answer your question,
no, I have not been won over.

207
00:12:48,350 --> 00:12:52,888
♪ Something's
got to give, hey ♪♪

208
00:12:53,889 --> 00:12:55,891
Jonathan Chase,
how you doing?

209
00:12:55,891 --> 00:12:57,893
Where's my lawyer?

210
00:12:57,893 --> 00:13:01,363
Well you see, he was--he
got caught up in a--he had a--

211
00:13:01,363 --> 00:13:04,366
Mario,
where's my lawyer?

212
00:13:04,366 --> 00:13:05,868
Jonathan, I called
him earlier today.

213
00:13:05,868 --> 00:13:07,369
I don't know what happened.

214
00:13:07,369 --> 00:13:08,871
I just don't know
what happened.

215
00:13:08,871 --> 00:13:12,374
Mr. Chase, can I get you
to have a seat please, sir?

216
00:13:15,377 --> 00:13:17,379
Okay, look.
Here's where we are.

217
00:13:17,379 --> 00:13:18,881
This is where you stand.

218
00:13:18,881 --> 00:13:20,883
It's kind of got a lot
of evidence, but look,

219
00:13:20,883 --> 00:13:24,336
we can work through
this as a team, okay?

220
00:13:27,339 --> 00:13:29,842
All rise
and come to order.

221
00:13:29,842 --> 00:13:32,344
District Court 278
is now in session.

222
00:13:32,344 --> 00:13:34,346
The Honorable Judge Reeves
is presiding.

223
00:13:34,346 --> 00:13:36,348
All have a seat, please.

224
00:13:36,849 --> 00:13:37,349
Today, we're going
to do the docket,

225
00:13:37,850 --> 00:13:40,853
the State versus
Jonathan Chase.

226
00:13:41,854 --> 00:13:43,856
Your Honor,
I need a new attorney!

227
00:13:43,856 --> 00:13:46,325
Sit down or you're
going to county jail.

228
00:13:46,325 --> 00:13:47,193
Wow, just relax,
all right?

229
00:13:47,193 --> 00:13:48,661
We'll take care of this.

230
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:50,663
Just let me handle this.

231
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:53,165
Your Honor, may I
approach the bench?

232
00:13:53,165 --> 00:13:54,667
Please come forward.

233
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:55,668
Your Honor,
I apologize for that.

234
00:13:56,168 --> 00:13:58,671
My name is Mr. Mark McClain
and Mr. Bauman

235
00:13:58,671 --> 00:14:01,173
from Bauman and Associates,
he had a family emergency.

236
00:14:01,674 --> 00:14:02,675
Emergency?

237
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:05,010
This is an emergency!

238
00:14:05,010 --> 00:14:06,011
Curb that defendant!

239
00:14:06,011 --> 00:14:09,381
Look, I don't need this
new recruit paralegal

240
00:14:09,381 --> 00:14:10,382
trying to represent me!

241
00:14:10,883 --> 00:14:12,384
Where's my lawyer?

242
00:14:12,384 --> 00:14:14,386
(Judge Reeves)
Bailiff, take this defendant
into custody right now.

243
00:14:14,887 --> 00:14:15,888
Mr. Chase, you've been
ordered by the court

244
00:14:15,888 --> 00:14:16,889
to be taken into custody.

245
00:14:17,389 --> 00:14:18,390
You can put your hands
behind your back;

246
00:14:18,390 --> 00:14:19,391
keep them away
from your pockets.

247
00:14:19,391 --> 00:14:20,392
Sit down!

248
00:14:20,893 --> 00:14:21,894
(Mark)
Oh, this is not good.

249
00:14:21,894 --> 00:14:22,895
I told you not
to be saying anything.

250
00:14:22,895 --> 00:14:23,395
Just keep your mouth shut,
okay?

251
00:14:23,395 --> 00:14:25,898
Just be quiet.

252
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:31,403
You tell Bauman
you reap what you sow.

253
00:14:34,406 --> 00:14:45,417
♪♪♪

254
00:15:10,075 --> 00:15:11,577
(Joshua)
Man, Chris, I ain't
even going to lie.

255
00:15:11,577 --> 00:15:12,912
I'm impressed, man.

256
00:15:13,495 --> 00:15:15,497
You really got it
going on in here.

257
00:15:15,781 --> 00:15:17,783
Thank you.

258
00:15:17,783 --> 00:15:20,586
University of Monroe, huh?

259
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:23,589
It's a nice office, man.

