00:15:25,591 --> 00:15:29,094
Look here, I've got a meeting
with my staff in a few minutes

261
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:32,348
and also I've arranged for
a taxi to come and pick you up.

262
00:15:32,348 --> 00:15:33,766
Man, a taxi?

263
00:15:35,267 --> 00:15:37,720
Look Joshua, Mom's been
looking forward to seeing you

264
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:39,772
for a real long time.

265
00:15:39,772 --> 00:15:41,607
Last time you let her down.

266
00:15:41,607 --> 00:15:43,943
Don't do it again.

267
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:45,194
You understand?

268
00:15:45,194 --> 00:15:46,695
Yeah man, look,
don't worry,

269
00:15:46,695 --> 00:15:48,697
I'm not messing anything up.

270
00:15:48,697 --> 00:15:50,699
I couldn't mess it
up this time, dude.

271
00:15:50,699 --> 00:15:57,373
Look, I got a son
to look after now, man.

272
00:15:57,873 --> 00:15:58,874
A son?

273
00:15:58,874 --> 00:16:00,659
You never mentioned
before that you had a son.

274
00:16:00,659 --> 00:16:02,461
Yeah, man,
that's my little boy.

275
00:16:02,461 --> 00:16:03,963
He's growing up.

276
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:05,331
You know, I've been gone
for a long time now,

277
00:16:05,831 --> 00:16:10,169
so I'm going to do whatever
I can to make it up to him.

278
00:16:11,170 --> 00:16:14,673
Well, I know he's looking
forward to having his daddy

279
00:16:14,673 --> 00:16:15,674
in his life.

280
00:16:18,644 --> 00:16:21,513
(Joshua)
Being adopted seemed to be
the hardest transition for me

281
00:16:21,513 --> 00:16:25,651
to handle, a lifelong
road of uncertainty.

282
00:16:25,651 --> 00:16:29,021
Losing dad left
emptiness in my heart.

283
00:16:29,021 --> 00:16:30,522
I'd give anything to
extinguish this deep,

284
00:16:30,522 --> 00:16:36,528
innermost root of loneliness,
to find a true peace.

285
00:16:37,529 --> 00:16:41,033
No wonder after 11 years
of hard time incarceration

286
00:16:41,033 --> 00:16:44,536
I still feel locked up inside.

287
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:56,548
[phone ringing]

288
00:16:59,551 --> 00:17:00,052
Hello?

289
00:17:00,052 --> 00:17:01,553
(female #4)
Mom?

290
00:17:01,970 --> 00:17:04,056
Sarah,
is that you?

291
00:17:07,276 --> 00:17:09,028
Sarah?

292
00:17:09,028 --> 00:17:10,612
It's me, I'm here.

293
00:17:10,612 --> 00:17:12,815
Baby, what's wrong?

294
00:17:12,815 --> 00:17:13,732
I can't take it anymore.

295
00:17:13,732 --> 00:17:17,069
Our marriage
is falling apart.

296
00:17:17,069 --> 00:17:18,570
Sarah, what's
exactly going on?

297
00:17:18,821 --> 00:17:20,572
Talk to me.

298
00:17:20,572 --> 00:17:21,573
I don't know.
I don't know.

299
00:17:21,573 --> 00:17:23,575
I don't understand.

300
00:17:23,575 --> 00:17:27,496
It seems like the more I try,
the worse our relationship gets.

301
00:17:27,496 --> 00:17:30,332
I mean, I cooked him dinner
and he stood me up again.

302
00:17:30,332 --> 00:17:30,499
Mm-hmm.

303
00:17:32,668 --> 00:17:37,139
Sarah, I know it's hard,
but you can't lose heart.

304
00:17:37,139 --> 00:17:39,141
There is hope.

305
00:17:39,141 --> 00:17:41,343
I tell you what,

306
00:17:41,343 --> 00:17:43,429
why don't we meet tomorrow
evening for dinner

307
00:17:43,429 --> 00:17:44,980
at our favorite spot?

308
00:17:45,347 --> 00:17:46,398
I'd like that.
Thanks, mom.

309
00:17:46,899 --> 00:17:48,767
I really appreciate that.

310
00:17:48,767 --> 00:17:50,769
But please
do not tell Christopher

311
00:17:50,769 --> 00:17:52,771
that I talked to you
about this.

312
00:17:52,771 --> 00:17:54,323
I promise.

313
00:17:54,907 --> 00:17:58,494
All right, I'll see you tomorrow
if it's the Lord's will.

314
00:17:58,861 --> 00:17:59,778
Okay.

315
00:17:59,778 --> 00:18:02,281
Okay.
Bye-bye.

316
00:18:02,281 --> 00:18:04,283
Okay, bye.

317
00:18:06,785 --> 00:18:07,419
[door bell ringing]

318
00:18:09,004 --> 00:18:11,006
Come in!

319
00:18:13,876 --> 00:18:15,677
(Joshua)
Mama.

320
00:18:16,178 --> 00:18:18,180
Oh, Joshua.

321
00:18:18,180 --> 00:18:22,184
Oh, thank the Lord
you made it home safely.

322
00:18:23,185 --> 00:18:24,186
It's good
to see you, Mama.

323
00:18:24,186 --> 00:18:25,187
Oh, it's good
to see you too.

324
00:18:25,187 --> 00:18:27,189
And you look so good!

325
00:18:27,189 --> 00:18:28,190
Oh man, I feel good.

326
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:29,691
It's nice to be home.

327
00:18:29,691 --> 00:18:30,692
Oh, how was
your train ride?

328
00:18:30,692 --> 00:18:33,695
Train ride was good.
It was refreshing, you know?

329
00:18:33,695 --> 00:18:36,698
And the ride with Chris,
that was a little tough.

330
00:18:36,698 --> 00:18:38,200
That's another story.

331
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:41,120
Son,
it's not Christopher.

332
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:44,406
You know, he's carrying
his own burdens, you know?

333
00:18:44,406 --> 00:18:48,043
And until both of you
totally surrender to God,

334
00:18:48,410 --> 00:18:49,495
your problems
are going to overcome you

335
00:18:49,495 --> 00:18:52,998
instead of you
overcoming your problems.

336
00:18:52,998 --> 00:18:53,999
I know, Ma.

337
00:18:53,999 --> 00:18:55,501
You know,
I'm just getting home.

338
00:18:55,501 --> 00:18:59,338
We'll get to that,
but it's just--

339
00:18:59,838 --> 00:19:00,339
Nothing.

340
00:19:00,839 --> 00:19:02,257
I'll tell you what,
it's one thing to know

341
00:19:02,257 --> 00:19:04,643
and it's another thing to obey.

342
00:19:05,144 --> 00:19:06,645
Anyway, come on in
and have some of my

343
00:19:06,645 --> 00:19:09,731
good ol' homemade
cranberry bread.

344
00:19:12,067 --> 00:19:13,402
Whew.

345
00:19:16,405 --> 00:19:16,905
Okay.

346
00:19:16,905 --> 00:19:19,441
Where are we?

347
00:19:19,441 --> 00:19:21,360
Total new clients
this week: 18.

348
00:19:21,360 --> 00:19:25,280
Total retainer's fee:
$47,250.

349
00:19:25,280 --> 00:19:27,699
And the bad news
is this Mr. Chase guy,

350
00:19:27,699 --> 00:19:29,918
he doesn't want to accept any
plea bargains and he's demanding

351
00:19:29,918 --> 00:19:31,703
that you specifically
represent him in court.

352
00:19:31,703 --> 00:19:33,672
He'll plea.

353
00:19:33,672 --> 00:19:34,756
No, listen.

354
00:19:34,756 --> 00:19:35,624
Look, he's not accepting
any plea bargains

355
00:19:35,924 --> 00:19:37,593
and he's not playing around.

356
00:19:38,093 --> 00:19:40,512
Look, I just got off the phone
with some of his boys

357
00:19:40,512 --> 00:19:43,515
and they're demanding 15 of
the $25,000 refunded.

358
00:19:43,515 --> 00:19:47,186
Seems to me like you're
being a little sensitive here.

359
00:19:47,186 --> 00:19:48,687
Or maybe I'm just trying
to do my job

360
00:19:48,687 --> 00:19:50,856
building
a respectable reputation.

361
00:19:50,856 --> 00:19:53,392
Maybe, but understand this,
this is a respectable law firm.

362
00:19:53,392 --> 00:19:55,777
Look, I understand
Mr. Bauman.

363
00:19:55,777 --> 00:19:59,648
But look, I won't compromise
my integrity to lose my family.

364
00:19:59,648 --> 00:20:00,115
Stop!

365
00:20:00,115 --> 00:20:02,234
Are you calling me a crook?

366
00:20:02,234 --> 00:20:04,286
You're fresh off
the college block!

367
00:20:04,286 --> 00:20:05,787
Let me tell you
something, rookie.

368
00:20:05,787 --> 00:20:07,322
You need to adjust
to the program.

369
00:20:07,906 --> 00:20:10,909
Well, this program needs to
be winding down by 7 o'clock!

370
00:20:10,909 --> 00:20:11,460
Gentlemen, please!

371
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:13,912
It's Friday.

372
00:20:13,912 --> 00:20:17,382
Let's just calm down,
finish the briefing

373
00:20:17,382 --> 00:20:19,885
so we can all go home
and enjoy the weekend.

374
00:20:19,885 --> 00:20:22,304
Okay?

375
00:20:22,804 --> 00:20:23,805
Whatever.

376
00:20:24,306 --> 00:20:26,008
(Christopher)
Look here rookie,

377
00:20:26,008 --> 00:20:28,393
you need to go handle
your business.

378
00:20:31,897 --> 00:20:33,849
Okay.

379
00:20:33,849 --> 00:20:37,319
Documents complete.

380
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:40,322
This case is ready for
trial Monday morning.

381
00:20:40,322 --> 00:20:41,323
All right.

382
00:20:41,823 --> 00:20:44,192
Thanks so much for staying
late to finish the briefing.

383
00:20:44,192 --> 00:20:45,611
No problem.

384
00:20:45,611 --> 00:20:47,446
I talked to Ron earlier
and let him know the importance

385
00:20:47,446 --> 00:20:51,917
of this case and he knew I was
going to work late tonight.

386
00:20:51,917 --> 00:20:52,834
You know what?

387
00:20:52,834 --> 00:20:54,836
Since you've been
working late all week,

388
00:20:54,836 --> 00:20:57,205
why don't you take Monday off?

389
00:20:57,205 --> 00:21:00,876
No, why don't
you take Monday off?

390
00:21:01,376 --> 00:21:06,131
Your wife really
deserves it, Christopher.

391
00:21:18,393 --> 00:21:23,031
[phone ringing]

392
00:21:30,289 --> 00:21:31,290
[answering machine beeping]

393
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:32,791
(Christopher)
Sarah, hey.

394
00:21:32,791 --> 00:21:34,209
I'll be home late again.

395
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:39,414
I had some important business
to finish at the office.

396
00:21:42,918 --> 00:21:44,920
Business.

397
00:21:44,920 --> 00:21:49,141
Always the priority.

398
00:22:22,924 --> 00:22:28,213
♪♪♪

399
00:22:41,026 --> 00:22:44,029
(Sarah)
Dear Christopher,
it's been 4 1/2 years

400
00:22:44,029 --> 00:22:47,949
since we had true
quality time together.

401
00:22:49,401 --> 00:22:52,788
I miss your small but
spur-of-the-moment surprises.

402
00:22:52,788 --> 00:22:54,790
I've forgotten the last time
we even prayed together,

403
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:58,710
not to mention our lack
of daily communication,

404
00:22:58,710 --> 00:23:02,164
which only consists of
"Good morning" or "Good night."

405
00:23:02,164 --> 00:23:05,884
Your law practice has
taken over our whole life.

406
00:23:05,884 --> 00:23:08,887
Do you even care that
we're drifting apart?

407
00:23:09,304 --> 00:23:13,809
Sarah, your wife.

408
00:23:14,810 --> 00:23:29,825
♪♪♪

409
00:23:33,445 --> 00:23:48,627
♪♪♪

410
00:23:49,628 --> 00:23:59,304
♪♪♪

411
00:24:01,807 --> 00:24:06,311
[phone ringing]

412
00:24:07,779 --> 00:24:11,783
Hello?
Hello?

413
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:13,702
Christopher?

414
00:24:13,702 --> 00:24:15,704
Christopher,
I am sick and tired

415
00:24:15,704 --> 00:24:18,156
of all these phone calls
and hang-ups.

416
00:24:18,156 --> 00:24:20,459
Christopher?

417
00:24:23,545 --> 00:24:26,248
He's gone!

418
00:24:27,249 --> 00:24:28,250
I'm finished.

419
00:24:28,250 --> 00:24:30,719
I am done!

420
00:24:34,556 --> 00:24:39,978
♪♪♪

421
00:24:44,766 --> 00:24:47,769
[door bell rings]

422
00:24:49,271 --> 00:24:50,272
Mrs. Bauman? Yes.

423
00:24:50,272 --> 00:24:52,157
You have
a delivery.

424
00:24:52,157 --> 00:24:53,158
Thank you.

425
00:24:53,658 --> 00:24:55,610
You must be very
special to someone.

426
00:24:56,111 --> 00:24:57,112
I suppose I am.

427
00:24:57,612 --> 00:24:58,113
Well you have
a nice day, ma'am.

428
00:24:58,113 --> 00:25:00,115
Thank you, you too.

429
00:25:10,091 --> 00:25:13,545
What?
What?

430
00:25:17,382 --> 00:25:20,352
[glass shattering]

431
00:25:27,108 --> 00:25:30,612
(female #5)
Girl, I am so sorry about
this mess with your husband.

432
00:25:31,112 --> 00:25:32,113
Just men.

433
00:25:32,614 --> 00:25:35,233
You need to divorce
that creep.

434
00:25:35,734 --> 00:25:38,036
And considering
being threatened,

435
00:25:38,036 --> 00:25:41,907
I'd take out a good life
insurance policy if I were you.

436
00:25:41,907 --> 00:25:44,709
No, I don't think
Why not? I could do that.

437
00:25:44,709 --> 00:25:47,579
Well, for one, there's no
divorce lawyer in Seguin

438
00:25:47,579 --> 00:25:49,464
that's going to represent me.

439
00:25:49,464 --> 00:25:53,218
Two, you need money,
that which I don't have.

440
00:25:53,218 --> 00:25:56,555
Well, listen, you let
me take care of all that,

441
00:25:56,555 --> 00:25:58,506
including the life insurance.

442
00:25:58,506 --> 00:26:00,508
I'll set you up with
a good attorney.

443
00:26:00,508 --> 00:26:03,345
A local friend of mine is
a life insurance agent.

444
00:26:03,345 --> 00:26:04,346
I'll cover the costs. No.

445
00:26:04,346 --> 00:26:06,264
Ah, Ah, Ah.

446
00:26:06,264 --> 00:26:09,434
You just remember that
anything happens to him,

447
00:26:09,434 --> 00:26:11,603
I get half the policy, deal?

448
00:26:11,603 --> 00:26:14,105
Deal.
You're so silly.

449
00:26:14,105 --> 00:26:16,107
Shush, here comes
my mother-in-law.

450
00:26:16,107 --> 00:26:18,944
I don't want her to think that
we're plotting against her son.

451
00:26:18,944 --> 00:26:20,445
Ma?

452
00:26:20,445 --> 00:26:21,947
Hi.

453
00:26:21,947 --> 00:26:23,448
Hi, Sarah.

454
00:26:23,448 --> 00:26:24,950
Sorry I'm a little bit late.

455
00:26:24,950 --> 00:26:25,450
It's okay.

456
00:26:26,952 --> 00:26:27,953
How are you?

457
00:26:27,953 --> 00:26:29,955
I'm not doing too good.

458
00:26:30,455 --> 00:26:31,957
But this is my friend, Joey.

459
00:26:32,457 --> 00:26:33,458
Joey Perkins.

460
00:26:33,458 --> 00:26:35,844
Joey, this is my
mother-in-law, Lucille Bauman.

461
00:26:35,844 --> 00:26:37,345
Nice to meet you.

462
00:26:37,345 --> 00:26:42,050
So tell me, is it Joey
or Joanna Perkins?

463
00:26:42,050 --> 00:26:46,271
Well, my birth name
is Joanna Perkins,

464
00:26:46,271 --> 00:26:48,807
but that's not what I go by.

465
00:26:48,807 --> 00:26:51,192
Well, if you don't mind,
I'd rather call you

466
00:26:51,192 --> 00:26:53,945
by your birth name,
Joanna Perkins.

467
00:26:53,945 --> 00:26:55,814
Is that fine?

468
00:26:55,814 --> 00:26:57,816
That's fine.

469
00:26:57,816 --> 00:26:59,067
(male #4)
Hi, are we ready to order?

470
00:26:59,067 --> 00:27:00,068
You know what?

471
00:27:00,568 --> 00:27:02,954
I don't have much of
an appetite right now.

472
00:27:02,954 --> 00:27:03,822
I'll pass also.

473
00:27:04,322 --> 00:27:06,324
Okay, if you need anything else,
just let me know.

474
00:27:06,825 --> 00:27:08,326
Okay, thank you.

475
00:27:08,326 --> 00:27:09,661
Okay.

476
00:27:09,661 --> 00:27:12,163
What's really going on Sarah?

477
00:27:12,163 --> 00:27:14,582
Well, I moved out.

478
00:27:14,582 --> 00:27:16,418
And mom, you know how
much I love Christopher,

479
00:27:16,835 --> 00:27:21,840
but I'm scared, angry,
and I'm just fed up of all of

480
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:25,060
the threatening phone calls
and of the angry clients.

481
00:27:25,560 --> 00:27:28,396
I mean, besides,
I don't ever see him.

482
00:27:28,396 --> 00:27:30,148
So where are you staying?

483
00:27:30,148 --> 00:27:33,101
Well, after this last
episode, my friend Joey,

484
00:27:33,601 --> 00:27:36,404
Joanna, she has opened up her
home to me and I'm going to stay

485
00:27:36,404 --> 00:27:39,157
with her until I
get an apartment.

486
00:27:39,157 --> 00:27:40,992
Ma'am, I don't
mean to intervene,

487
00:27:40,992 --> 00:27:43,995
but I've known Sarah
for a very long time.

488
00:27:43,995 --> 00:27:46,331
And for what
she's been going through,

489
00:27:46,331 --> 00:27:48,283
she deserves better.

490
00:27:48,283 --> 00:27:52,704
And how do you
define better?

491
00:27:52,704 --> 00:27:58,426
Happiness, security, love.

492
00:27:58,426 --> 00:28:02,430
Joanna, when you look
deep within yourself,

493
00:28:02,430 --> 00:28:04,349
are you truly happy?

494
00:28:06,267 --> 00:28:09,104
Truthfully?

495
00:28:09,104 --> 00:28:10,472
No.

496
00:28:10,472 --> 00:28:13,725
I guess once my father stopped
showing me he cared about me,

497
00:28:13,725 --> 00:28:16,861
I just kind of gave up.

498
00:28:18,229 --> 00:28:23,401
Had he been there for me, well,
let's just say I might not

499
00:28:23,401 --> 00:28:26,821
have turned out
like I am today.

500
00:28:27,322 --> 00:28:30,542
God's love has always
been there for you, Joanna.

501
00:28:31,042 --> 00:28:33,878
It's just that you haven't
allowed the Word to give you

502
00:28:34,329 --> 00:28:39,551
the peace, joy, and true
happiness that only he can give.

503
00:28:40,051 --> 00:28:45,890
Joanna, Jesus Christ
can change your life.

504
00:28:45,890 --> 00:28:47,892
I'll see you later, Sarah.

505
00:28:48,309 --> 00:28:49,677
Okay.

506
00:28:52,180 --> 00:28:55,850
I didn't mean to
offend your friend, Sarah,

507
00:28:55,850 --> 00:28:58,353
but the truth must
come to light.

508
00:28:58,353 --> 00:28:59,854
I know, Mom.
Don't worry about it.

509
00:29:00,355 --> 00:29:00,355
She'll be okay.

510
00:29:00,855 --> 00:29:02,857
She'll be fine.

511
00:29:02,857 --> 00:29:04,859
I sure hope so.

512
00:29:09,831 --> 00:29:14,252
Speaking of the truth,
Sarah, you listen to me.

513
00:29:14,252 --> 00:29:17,122
You are a bright woman

514
00:29:17,122 --> 00:29:21,543
and you can't let
your friends influence you.

515
00:29:21,543 --> 00:29:24,045
Trust me,
I know how you feel.

516
00:29:24,045 --> 00:29:29,434
In our eyes, it seems right
to divorce our husbands

517
00:29:29,434 --> 00:29:32,720
when things don't
seem to be going right.

518
00:29:32,720 --> 00:29:36,357
But that's not God's way.

519
00:29:36,357 --> 00:29:38,726
He hates divorce.

520
00:29:38,726 --> 00:29:40,228
Yes, but I'm not
