1613
01:33:04,078 --> 01:33:06,581
Oh, thank the Lord.

1614
01:33:06,581 --> 01:33:10,034
And yes, doctor, God does hear
the prayers of his children.

1615
01:33:10,534 --> 01:33:13,504
You know, I have to admit,
I've never met anyone that was

1616
01:33:13,504 --> 01:33:14,956
so passionate and sincere
about their relationship

1617
01:33:15,456 --> 01:33:17,925
with Jesus Christ as you are.

1618
01:33:18,376 --> 01:33:20,211
You've been an
encouragement to me.

1619
01:33:20,211 --> 01:33:22,129
Well, to God be the glory.

1620
01:33:22,129 --> 01:33:25,049
And thank you, doctor, for
everything that you've done.

1621
01:33:25,549 --> 01:33:26,968
My pleasure.

1622
01:33:26,968 --> 01:33:29,470
Christopher's doing well
and resting in recovery.

1623
01:33:29,470 --> 01:33:31,389
You can see him shortly.

1624
01:33:31,389 --> 01:33:33,391
Okay. Okay.

1625
01:33:33,391 --> 01:33:34,392
You're welcome.
Thank you so much.

1626
01:33:34,392 --> 01:33:36,310
And God bless you, doctor.

1627
01:33:36,310 --> 01:33:38,813
God bless you also.

1628
01:33:46,737 --> 01:33:50,041
Mr. Ramone, how
are you this morning?

1629
01:33:50,041 --> 01:33:52,793
Merry Christmas,
Mr. Ramone.

1630
01:33:52,793 --> 01:33:54,211
Hey, what's so
merry about it?

1631
01:33:54,211 --> 01:33:57,164
It's just another day.

1632
01:33:57,164 --> 01:33:58,666
It's a holy holiday.

1633
01:33:58,666 --> 01:34:01,168
It's something
to be happy about.

1634
01:34:01,168 --> 01:34:04,171
Well, anyway, did you
enjoy your morning stroll?

1635
01:34:04,171 --> 01:34:06,590
No.

1636
01:34:13,481 --> 01:34:14,482
Good morning.

1637
01:34:14,482 --> 01:34:16,067
I'm here to see
Christopher Bauman.

1638
01:34:16,067 --> 01:34:17,018
I'm Sarah Bauman.

1639
01:34:17,485 --> 01:34:19,904
Oh, yes, your mother-in-law
said you might be stopping by.

1640
01:34:19,904 --> 01:34:23,574
